{
  "stem": "22047.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Actually, the first thing we saw before we went to the gates of Dachau was this train load of bodies.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And that was traumatic enough without having gone into the-- into the compound itself.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got to the gate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is what the gate looked like when we arrived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was the-- actually, it wasn't the gate that most of the prisoners were taken into.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was another gate on the other side of the camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And having been-- seen these bodies on this train was-- was pretty traumatic.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But then going into the camp, to just-- to see this unbelievable scene of-- of death.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It-- it was the 29th of April.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was- had been cold, so we didn't-- it wasn't as terrible smelling as it might have been.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the smell-- you could smell death in this camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And as I mentioned, having met this Belgian officer and was taken around a camp and to see one absolutely revolting scene after another-- the barracks where they were-- the prisoners were.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were-- a lot of them were so sick, they couldn't move hardly.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Some who were able to move were so emaciated from the lack of sustenance-- and the-- the piles of bodies all over the camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The-- the crematorium, as I said, that had this stack of bodies that hadn't-- they hadn't been able to-- to burn.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It turned out that they'd run out of fuel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the train load of people that were out on the tracks outside the compound were brought there, presumably to be cremated.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Some had, I guess, had died in other camps, in maybe in some of the satellites.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
